1. Python 2.7.x or 3.x is required to run aloft. 
To check your python version:
	$ python --version

To download the latest version of Python, visit www.python.org

2. Download the ALoFT package from [???].
	$ wget [FTP SITE HERE]
	$ gunzip aloft

3. Run install.py to compile all dependencies that aloft requires:
    $ cd aloft
    $ python install.py
This will install VAT, our gerp score caching module, the networkx module, 
and the reference files (located in aloft/data) required to run aloft.

4. After compiling, aloft.py is the main script to run.
To see the help screen:
	$ python aloft.py -h

For more complete information on running ALoFT, see QUICKSTART or README.

